Can this recipe be named optee-os-nuvoton.bb, just like u-boot-nuvoton/linux-nuvoton, etc?
Done. I have modified this recipe name as optee-os-nuvoton.bb.

Can we use the optee recipe from Yocto instead?

https://git.yoctoproject.org/meta-arm/tree/meta-arm/recipes-security/optee

We create these optee relevant recipes that refer to OP-TEE GitHub.
Due to we cannot find any optee recipes from OpenBMC GitHub.
Thus, we need your help to merge those recipes with our TEE OS for Nuvoton npmc8xx.
The recipe folder I linked has support for building OP-TEE from GitHub. It's not currently in OpenBMC, but we can pull in the meta-arm layer from Yocto in order to have it available.
Thanks your great support to pull in the meta-arm layer from Yocto into openbmc subtree. We will modify this recipe through right path for supporting OP-TEE when meta-arm layer be pulled in.

Hi Dhananjay Phadke,

Thanks your help to review and suggestion.
We have modified the recipe name as optee-os-nuvoton.bb.
Please help us to review it again. Thank you.

Best regards,
Tim
Why are you putting a branch in here but then also putting one in SRC_URI?
We really want to take yet another fork of a repo?  Can we get some explanation of what this even does?  I have no idea what "OP-TEE Trusted OS" means.
Thanks. We will remove REPO and keep using SRC_URI only.

Yes, you're right. Not necessary fork of a repo. We think that we can use meta-arm layer as base (instead of Nuvoton GitHub) and add NPCM8XX modifications as patches. When meta-arm layer be pulled in, we will modify this recipe. Thanks.

OP-TEE is a Trusted Execution Environment (TEE) designed as companion to a non-secure Linux kernel running on Arm. Cortex-A cores using the TrustZone technology.

A Linux user space supplicant daemon (tee-supplicant) responsible for remote services expected by the TEE OS.

OP-TEE is divided in various components:
These components are available from several git repositories. The main ones are build, optee_os, optee_client, optee_test, optee_examples and the Linux kernel TEE framework.

From https://optee.readthedocs.io/en/latest/general/about.html
Wut? A binary file?
Thanks for reviewing. This binary should not exist in metadata. We will remove it.
Why do we want a test suite?

Yes, we like to include the optee test for to the NPCM8XX, and we see it already include in the meta-arm. We will modify this recipe when meta-arm layer be pulled in.
https://git.yoctoproject.org/meta-arm/tree/meta-arm/recipes-security/optee

Generally we don't accept recipes pointing outside the openbmc organization.  We might accept some pointing to a nuvoton organization for some BSP support, but this does not appear to be that.  Does this belong upstream in meta-security instead?
This belongs in Yocto's meta-arm layer (they already have a recipe for OP-TEE there actually)

Yes, we need to use right path for building OP-TEE.
We will modify this recipe when meta-arm layer be pulled in. Thanks.

Hi Benjamin,

We had provided new recipe of optee_os binary release for npcm8xx.
Please help us to review and merge it for npcm8xx platform. Thanks a lot.

Best regards,
Tim
Now that meta-arm layer is added, wouldn't this be a .bbappend to it instead of being recipe? If it has to be a new recipe, it would need different name like optee-os-nuvoton as commented before?
Thanks your review and suggestion. We will use meta-arm layer as base then append our platform modification for your review it again. Thanks.

If you have too many patches that are not yet merged in upstream optee-os, might be better to create a mirror under openbmc project as suggested by others.

Currently the delta just looks 11 patches, mostly adding npcm plat code. Are there any drivers planned?

https://github.com/OP-TEE/optee_os/compare/master...Nuvoton-Israel:optee_os:nuvoton

As you said that, mostly adding npcm plat code. No any drivers is planned.
We need to check which way to integrate it into meta-arm layer of openbmc.
Same suggestion as the ATF recipe. Thanks.
I don't think we should be accepting a binary blob.  Why is it a binary blob and not compiled from a real recipe?
Yep, same comment as the ATF recipe
Thanks your review and suggestion. We will use meta-arm layer as base then append our platform modification for your review it again. Thanks.

Hi Benjamin and Patrick,

We have created new recipe 2.6.0 that using official ATF GitHub release tag TF-A v2.6, instead our GitHub. For support npcm8xx in ATF, we add nuvoton platform related modification as patches, but according patch policy, we got build failed in repotest. Could we add those patches into repotest table to fix this kind of failure?

Best regards,
Tim

Sorry, correct above comment for OPTEE.

Thanks your suggestion. We're working rebase OPTEE to 3.18 then will submit new recipe and bbappend it. Thank you.
please add overrides to these so it only affects npcm8xx
Thanks your review and suggestion for this bbappend, I have added overrides for npcm8xx only.

Is there any Nuvoton customization to ta-devkit? Otherwise, downstream layer can just use the one provided by meta-arm, since it's same version. This is same as any target needing optee-client, unless there's any new Nuvoton header, can just use the recipe from meta-arm.

At the beginning, we only add optee-os_3.18.0.bbappend then bitbake optee-os build pass.
After that, we bitbake obmc-phosphor-image then we got build failure from optee-os-tadevkit_3.18.0.bb as below:

ERROR: optee-os-tadevkit-3.18.0-r0 do_compile: oe_runmake failed
| make: Entering directory '/home/tim/npcm-master/openbmc/build/evb-npcm845/tmp/work/evb_npcm845-openbmc-linux/optee-os-tadevkit/3.18.0-r0/git'
| mk/subdir.mk:183: core/arch/arm/plat-nuvoton/sub.mk: No such file or directory
| make: *** No rule to make target 'core/arch/arm/plat-nuvoton/sub.mk'.  Stop.
| make: Leaving directory '/home/tim/npcm-master/openbmc/build/evb-npcm845/tmp/work/evb_npcm845-openbmc-linux/optee-os-tadevkit/3.18.0-r0/git'
| ERROR: oe_runmake failed

From optee-os-tadevkit_3.18.0.bb that include "require optee-os_3.18.0.bb".
However, this recipe will include "require optee-os.inc" then SRC_URI will point to offical OPTEE github. That's why this build failure: No such folder "plat-nuvoton" exist.
Thus, I add optee-os-tadevkit_3.18.0.bbappend to fix this build failure then bitbake image can generate full image.
Ok looks like optee-test is getting enabled which has dependency on optee-tadevkit.
Just one small change left and then I'll +2
npcm8xx override on the SRCREVs too (here and the other file)
